Range check uses miss(v) in the error condition instead of only checking non-missing values.

Other-text (OE) validation is incorrect: it uses STRING(...) and a malformed RTRIM/LTRIM expression (comparison and string trimming are applied in the wrong order), so it will not reliably detect empty OE text for B1cx4_9_other.
instructions: Do not treat missing numeric cells as an error when the question is NotRequired. Replace the range/missing selection condition with a test that only flags out-of-range values for non-missing cells. Example: sel if B1cx4_dochecks = 1 AND NOT miss(v) AND (v < 0 OR v > 999).

Fix the OE presence check to operate on the actual string variable (or convert and compare properly). For example (if B1cx4_9_other is string):
COMPUTE B1cx4_oeerr = 0.
IF (B1cx4_dochecks = 1 AND NOT miss(B1cx4_9) AND B1cx4_9 > 0 AND RTRIM(LTRIM(B1cx4_9_other)) = '') B1cx4_oeerr = 1.
Then select cases where B1cx4_oeerr = 1 to list respid and the OE variable.

If B1cx4_9_other is numeric in your environment, convert it to string first and then trim/compare; but do so correctly (STRING(var,Fw.) produces a string representation of a number â€” compare that result to '' after trimming).

Keep the AutoSum check as-is but ensure the numeric types and rounding/precision are consistent with the Precision=3 requirement (if decimal places are allowed, consider using a tolerance when comparing sums).
